81078545.7 0081519-00002 AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (“Agreement”) is made and entered into this 23rd day of February, 2016, by and among WESTERN ANTELOPE BLUE SKY RANCH A LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Project 1”), SIERRA SOLAR GREENWORKS LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Project 2”), CENTRAL ANTELOPE DRY RANCH C LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, (“Project 3”), NORTH LANCASTER RANCH LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Project 4”), FTS DEVCO LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Project 5”), and SUSTAINABLE PROPERTY HOLDINGS, LLC (formerly FTS Property Holdings, LLC), a Delaware limited liability company (“SPH”), and SUSTAINABLE POWER SERVICES, LLC (formerly Tioga Services Company, LLC), a Delaware limited liability company. Project 1, Project 2, Project 3, Project 4 and Project 5 are sometimes referred to herein individually as a “Co- Owner” and collectively as “Co-Owners”. RECITALS A. Project 1 is developing a solar photovoltaic electricity generating facility with a rated capacity of 20 MW on a site near Lancaster, California (the “WABSRA Project”). B. Project 2 is developing a solar photovoltaic electricity generating facility with a rated capacity of 20 MW in the vicinity of the WABSRA Project (the “Sierra Solar Project”). C. Project 3 is developing a solar photovoltaic electricity generating facility with a rated capacity of 20 MW in the vicinity of the WABSRA Project (the “Central Antelope Project”). D. Project 4 is developing a solar photovoltaic electricity generating facility with a rated capacity of 20 MW in the vicinity of the WABSRA Project (the “North Lancaster Project”). E. Project 5 is developing a solar photovoltaic electricity generating facility with a rated capacity of 10 MW in the vicinity of the WABSRA Project (the “Devco Project”). F. The installed nameplate generating capacity of each of the WABSRA Project, Sierra Solar Project, Central Antelope Project, North Lancaster Project, and the Devco Project (each of which is referred to herein as a “Facility” and collectively as the “Facilities”), will be approximately: WABSRA Project: 20 MW Sierra Solar Project: 20 MW Central Antelope Project: 20 MW North Lancaster Project: 20 MW Devco Project: 10 MW -2- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 G. SPH owns, or has easements interests in and to, the real property upon which the Facilities are or will be constructed (as further defined below, the “Shared Real Property”), and joins this Agreement solely for purposes of conveying its interests in and to the Shared Real Property to the Co-Owners. H. As a result of this Agreement, the Co-Owners own or will own undivided interests in certain real and personal property acquired or to be acquired for their respective Facilities and wish to share the use and cost of certain electrical transmission, communications, structures and other facilities, and to engage the Operator to operate, maintain, repair and manage the foregoing, all in accordance with and subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. I. Sustainable Power Services, LLC, the Co-Owners and SPH are parties to that certain Shared Facilities Agreement dated October 30, 2014, as amended by the First Amendment to the Shared Facilities Agreement dated December 5, 2014 (collectively, the “Original Shared Facilities Agreement”). Sustainable Power Services, LLC, the Co-Owners and SPH desire to amend and completely restate the Original Shared Facilities Agreement in order to modify the description of a portion of the Transmission Line Easement, as set forth in Exhibit C-3 to the Original Shared Facilities Agreement, and as set forth below. NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the recitals, the premises, covenants and conditions contained herein, and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which the Co-Owners acknowledge, the Co-Owners agree as follows, and Sustainable Power Services, LLC, the Co-Owners and SPH amend and completely restate the Original Shared Facilities Agreement as follows: ARTICLE I DEFINITIONS, INTERPRETATIONS AND EXHIBITS 1.1 Definitions. As used in this Agreement, including the Recitals, and except as required by grammatical usage and apart from proper nouns, each capitalized term has the meaning given to it in this Agreement and in the Schedule of Definitions attached as Exhibit A. 1.2 Interpretation. In this Agreement, unless a clear, contrary intention appears: (a) the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (b) reference to any Person includes such Person’s successors and assigns but, in the case of a Co-Owner, only if such assigns are permits by this Agreement, and reference to a Person in a particular capacity excludes such Person in any other capacity; (c) reference to any gender includes each other gender; (d) reference to any agreement (including this Agreement), document or instrument means such agreement, document or instrument as amended or modified and in effect from time to time in accordance with the terms thereof and, if applicable, the terms of this Agreement; (e) reference to any Law means such Law as amended, modified, codified, or reenacted, in whole or in part, and in effect from time to time, including, if applicable, rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (f) reference to any Section means such Section of this Agreement, and references in any Section or definition to any clause means such clause of such Section or definition; (g) “hereunder,” “hereof,” “hereto” and words of similar import shall be deemed references to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular Section or other provision of this Agreement; (h) “including” means including without -3- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 limiting the generality of any description such term; and (i) relative to the determination of any period of time, “from” means “from and including”, “to” means “to be excluding” and “through” means “through and including”. 1.3 Incorporation of Recitals and Exhibits. The Recitals set forth in this Agreement and the Exhibits attached hereto are incorporated into this Agreement by reference for all purposes. ARTICLE II TERM OF AGREEMENT 2.1 Term. This Agreement is made effective as of October 30, 2014 (the “Effective Date”) and shall remain in force and effect until the earlier of (x) the date that is fifty (50) years after the Effective Date, and (y) the retirement and final disposition of all components of the Shared Facilities. Despite such earlier Effective Date, Exhibits C-1, C-3 and D have been updated to reflect circumstances existing on the date of this Agreement. 2.2 Payments on Termination. Upon termination of this Agreement, Co-Owners shall pay Operator any remaining balance owed for Operator’s costs incurred or irrevocably committed to be incurred pursuant to this Agreement as of the date of termination, within sixty (60) days following receipt of an invoice from Operator requiring such payment; provided that Operator shall use commercially reasonable efforts to minimize such costs. 2.3 Survival. Any obligations of one Co-Owner to another, including payment obligations and indemnity obligations, as a result of this Agreement which accrued prior to or as a result of termination of this Agreement shall survive termination of this Agreement. ARTICLE III SHARED FACILITIES AND REAL PROPERTY 3.1 Shared Facilities. The Co-Owners plan to procure, install and construct, or have procured, installed and constructed, certain facilities for electrical transmission, communications, structures and other facilities, as more particularly described in Exhibit B-1, which may be altered or reconstructed by amendment in accordance with this Agreement, for shared use by the Co- Owners (collectively, the “Shared Facilities”). 3.2 Shared Real Property. The Shared Facilities are or will be located on certain real property that, prior to the Effective Date, was owned in fee simple or subject to easement interests held by SPH. Pursuant to the conveyance documents, copies of which are provided in attached Exhibit C-1 (as the same may in the future be further amended, the “Shared Real Property Agreements”), SPH has (a) conveyed by grant deed fee title to each Co-Owner an undivided interest as tenants-in-common in and to that certain real property more particularly described in attached Exhibit C-2 (the “Substation Property”), and (b) granted to the Co-Owners in undivided interests a perpetual, nonexclusive easement in gross for a transmission line and related facilities with respect to certain real property more particularly described in attached Exhibit C-3 (the “Transmission Line Easement”). Together, the Substation Property and the Transmission Line -4- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 Easement, are referred to as the “Shared Real Property”). Together, the Shared Facilities and the Shared Real Property are referred to as the “Shared Assets”. 3.3 Access. Each Co-Owner shall have a non-exclusive right of access to the Shared Assets as necessary in order to ensure that Operator is meeting its obligations with respect to operation, maintenance and repair of such Shared Facilities, that Co-Owner’s Facility remains operational, and for the purposes contemplated in Article VII. Subject to the provisions of Section 13.1.4, in accessing the Shared Facilities or Shared Real Property a Co-Owner shall not unreasonably interfere with Operator’s operation, maintenance or repair of the Shared Facilities or of another Co-Owner’s Facility. No Co-Owner shall have access to another Co-Owner’s mechanical, structural and electrical/telecommunication components or equipment, or real property, that is not part of the Shared Assets. ARTICLE IV OWNERSHIP OF AND RIGHT TO USE SHARED ASSETS 4.1 Undivided Ownership Interests. Each Co-Owner owns or shall own an undivided interest, as a tenant-in-common, in the Shared Assets (and equal to its Proportionate Share as set forth and described in Exhibit B-2, and with such undivided interest of each Co-Owner being referred to in this Agreement as its “Ownership Interest”). 4.2 Undivided Use Interests. Each Co-Owner who has an Ownership Interest in the Shared Assets shall have an undivided right to the use or capacity of the Shared Facilities equal to its Proportionate Share therein, which right is exercisable upon the Commissioning Date of its Facility by such Co-Owner providing written notice to the Operator and to the other Co-Owners that the Commissioning Date has occurred, and provided that such Co-Owner has made the payment or payments set forth in Section 4.3, and that no Event of Default has occurred and is continuing with respect to such Co-Owner (once exercised, such undivided use interest of a Co- Owner is referred to in this Agreement as its “Undivided Use Interest”). For the avoidance of doubt, each Co-Owner whose Facility has not reached its Commissioning Date as of the Effective Date (and thus whose Proportionate Share in all Shared Assets is 0%) shall be deemed not to have exercised its Undivided Use Interest in the Shared Facilities (and as a result shall not be required to bear costs or expenses related to any Shared Facilities nor have the right to vote on matters unless otherwise set forth herein), but shall have the right to exercise its Undivided Use Interest as set forth in this Agreement. 4.2.1 Transmission Capacity. Each Co-Owner of the Shared Facilities shall be entitled to use its Undivided Use Interest in the Delivery Capability of the Transmission Line. In the event of a partial curtailment of Delivery Capability by Transmission Provider or a de-rating of the Transmission Line, each Co-Owner’s Undivided Use Interest will be reduced pro rata in accordance with its Proportionate Share for the duration of the curtailment or de-rating. In the event that the Delivery Capability of the Transmission Line exceeds the capability provided in the applicable Interconnection Agreement, with Transmission Owner’s and Transmission Provider’s consent and approval, each Co-Owner’s Undivided Use Interest will be increased pro rata in accordance with its Proportionate Share for so long as the Delivery Capability is in excess of the -5- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 capability provided in the Interconnection Agreements with Transmission Owner’s and Transmission Provider’s consent and approval. 4.2.2 Excess Capability. During periods in which a Co-Owner is not utilizing its full Undivided Use Interest in the Delivery Capability of the Transmission Line, the other Co- Owner may utilize more than its full Undivided Use Interest, subject to the operating limits of the Shared Facilities, so long as such usage does not interfere with or adversely affect the first Co- Owner’s energy schedules and deliveries, and provided that no payment obligation will attach to such utilization by a Co-Owner of more than its full Undivided Use Interest. 4.3 Reimbursement of Capital Costs. To compensate the Operator for having borne the costs and expenses of design, procurement, construction, installation and/or startup of the Shared Facilities, the following reimbursements have been made or shall be made based on the book value as of the end of the most recent month prior to the date the reimbursement payment is made: 4.3.1 On or before the Commissioning Date of the Sierra Solar Project, Project 2 shall have reimbursed the Project 1 for 22.22%, or 2/9, of such costs and expenses. 4.3.2 On or before the Commissioning Date of the Central Antelope Project, Project 3 shall have reimbursed the Project 1 for 22.22%, or 2/9, of such costs and expenses. 4.3.3 On or before the Commissioning Date of the North Lancaster Project, or any portion thereof, Project 4 shall have reimbursed the Project 1 for 22.22%, or 2/9, of such costs and expenses. 4.3.4 On or before the Commissioning Date of the Devco Project, Devco shall have reimbursed the Project 1 for such 11.11%, or 1/9, of such costs and expenses. 4.4 OandM Facilities Excluded. Each Co-Owner will construct and own, or has constructed and owns, an OandM Facility on real property owned by such Co-Owner. Each OandM Facility will be owned the respective Facility’s owner, and will not be a Shared Asset. ARTICLE V METERING AND LOSSES 5.1 Measurement. Each Co-Owner shall install and maintain, pursuant to its Interconnection Agreement, a dedicated revenue meter, with such meter being located prior to the Shared Facilities. 5.2 Losses on Transmission Line. Line Losses over the Shared Facilities shall be shared among the Co-Owners in proportion to each Co-Owners respective Ownership Interest. ARTICLE VI OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES. 6.1 Engagement of Operator. The Co-Owners hereby engage the Operator to manage, operate, maintain and repair the Shared Facilities and to perform other duties pertaining to the -6- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 Shared Assets (the “OandM Services”), all as set forth in this Agreement. The Operator accepts such engagement and agrees to perform such duties in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, to the extent that Operator is not licensed to perform any of its duties or obligations under this Agreement, Operator shall facilitate the Co-Owners in directly engaging acceptable licensed third parties to perform such duties or obligations. 6.2 Standards for Operator’s Performance. Operator shall perform the OandM Services in accordance with Good Utility Practice, the Material Project Agreements, the Shared Real Property Agreements, this Agreement and all other agreements relating to ownership, construction, operation and maintenance of the Shared Facilities, Applicable Laws and requirements of Governmental Authorities, including without limitation all Hazardous Materials Laws and all Environmental Laws, and all safety policies and procedures (collectively, the “Performance Standard”). 6.3 OandM Services. The Operator shall provide or cause to be provided the following services on behalf of each of the Co-Owners who have an Undivided Use Interest from and after the date such Co-Owner has notified Operator of its exercised right to an Undivided Use Interest in the Shared Facilities pursuant to Section 4.2 (the “OandM Services Commencement Date”): (a) Manage, supervise, operate, repair and maintain the Shared Assets in accordance with this Agreement, the Interconnection Agreements, and other Project Agreements, and in accordance with Good Utility Practice, the Approved Budget, including the day to day management of the Shared Assets; (b) pay and collect amounts due in connection with the Shared Assets including but not limited to taxes and assessments pursuant to Section 12.2, and maintain one or more bank accounts wherein funds received by the Operator in connection with its duties herein shall be maintained; (c) expend monies necessary for the management, operation, maintenance and repair of the Shared Facilities; (d) notify every Co-Owner of any notice (or any other information reasonably anticipated to affect the Co-Owners) received by Operator or received from any Co-Owner; (e) manage compliance with the Co-Owners’ rights in Shared Real Property in accordance with the Shared Real Property Agreements, including making payments required thereunder; provided that the Operator shall have no right to amend such rights in the Shared Real Property; and (f) with respect to the Shared Real Property and the Shared Facilities located on the Shared Real Property, oversee all investigations, studies, clean up, corrective action or response or remedial action required by any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative -7- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 order now or hereafter applicable to the use, operation or ownership of the Shared Real Property or the Shared Facilities locate on the Shared Real Property. 6.4 Scheduled Maintenance. Operator shall schedule maintenance and any planned outages of the Shared Facilities so as to minimize interference with Co-Owners’ scheduled energy deliveries. Maintenance and any planned outages of the Shared Facilities shall be scheduled, to the maximum extent possible, during scheduled maintenance outages of the Co-Owners’ Facilities and during hours of low insolation. Each Co-Owner will provide to the Operator and the other Co-Owners by January 1st of each year a schedule of planned maintenance outages on such Co- Owner’s Facility for the subsequent twelve-month period. Scheduled outages of the Shared Facilities that affect the business operations of one or more Co-Owners (each an “Affected Co- Owner”) will be subject to the mutual approval of each Affected Co-Owner, such approval not to be unreasonably withheld. Operator will seek to limit the duration of any outage, planned or unplanned, consistent with Good Utility Practice. 6.5 Unplanned Outages. Operator will notify Co-Owners of all emergency or unplanned outages of any of the Shared Facilities as soon as practicable, in accordance with Good Utility Practice, and will provide an estimated time of return of the Shared Facilities to service, or if not known, will keep Co-Owners advised regarding the status of same, 6.6 Emergency Conditions. In the event of an Emergency Condition involving the Shared Assets that could be reasonably expected by Operator to result in possible personal injury, loss of life, damage to or destruction of property, or danger to the public, the Operator shall, without the need for prior notification of the Co-Owners, take such action as may be reasonable and necessary, as determined in the sole discretion of the Operator, to prevent, avoid or mitigate such loss, and shall, as soon as reasonably practicable, report any such emergency, including the Operator’s response thereto, to the Co-Owners, and Operator shall be compensated by the Co- Owners for the costs of taking such actions in an amount equal to their Proportionate Share in the Shared Assets so affected. 6.7 OandM Costs. Costs of performing OandM Services (the “OandM costs”) shall include all payments made and expenses incurred by Operator in performing OandM Services (at cost and without markup), including but not limited to related overheads and applicable taxes, and costs (except insurance costs) related to ownership of the Shared Assets. 6.8 Budgeting Process. Each year during the term of this Agreement, Operator will prepare a forecast budget of OandM Costs for the following calendar year and will provide a copy to Co-Owners by October 31. Co-Owners will have thirty (30) days thereafter to review the forecast budget and discuss any concerns with the forecast budget with Operator. Operator’s implementation of the OandM Services consistent with the forecast budget is subject to Co-Owners’ prior approval, not to be unreasonably withheld (such approved forecast budget, the “Annual OandM Budget”) and each Co-Owner shall pay Operator 1/12 of its Proportionate Share of the Annual OandM Budget by the fifth (5th) day of each calendar month. 6.9 Extraordinary Maintenance. Each Co-Owner agrees to reimburse Operator for its share, in proportion to its Undivided Use Interest, of the costs of any maintenance or other services -8- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 required in the event of unusual or catastrophic circumstances, to the extent such costs were not included in the forecast budget for OandM Services (“Extraordinary Maintenance”). In such event, Operator will prepare a forecast budget for such Extraordinary Maintenance for Co-Owners’ review and performance of the Extraordinary Maintenance will be subject to Co-Owners’ prior approval, not to be unreasonably withheld, unless immediate action is required due to an Emergency Condition pursuant to Section 6.6. 6.10 Responsibility for OandM Costs. Each Co-Owner shall be responsible for its share, in proportion to its Undivided Use Interest, of OandM Costs, including its share of the costs of any Extraordinary Maintenance incurred by Operator, which shall be invoiced by Operator on a monthly basis. On or before the tenth (10th) day of each month, Operator shall invoice Co-Owners for their respective Undivided Use Interest of 1/12 of the amount of the current Annual OandM Budget, along with the costs of any Extraordinary Maintenance performed in the previous month. The invoices shall be delivered to Co-Owners as set forth in Section 16.14. Co-Owners shall pay such invoice within thirty (30) days of its receipt (the “Due Date”). Any amounts not paid by the Due Date shall be deemed delinquent and shall accrue interest at the then-effective prime rate of interest published under “Money Rates” by The Wall Street Journal, plus two percent per annum from the Due Date to the date of payment (the “Late Payment Rate”). For purposes of this Section 6.10 and for Section 6.11, “receipt” shall mean the date upon which the invoice is received in accordance with Section 16.14. In the event that any Due Date falls upon a weekend day or bank holiday, such payment shall be due and payable on the first Business Day immediately thereafter. 6.11 Exceeding Budget. In the event Operator incurs OandM Costs that exceed the Annual OandM Budget or costs of Extraordinary Maintenance that exceed the amount forecasted by more than $1,000.00 in any one month, Operator shall have the right to invoice Co-Owners for each Co-Owner’s share, in proportion to Co-Owner’s Undivided Use Interest or its Proportionate Share, as applicable, of such costs immediately upon incurring such costs and Co-Owner shall pay such invoice within thirty (30) days of its receipt. 6.12 Disputes. If a Co-Owner disputes the accuracy of all or any portion of an invoice, such Co-Owner shall, nevertheless, pay the full amount of the invoice (including the disputed portion) and submit to Operator a written statement detailing the items disputed. If Co-Owner prevails with respect to the disputed amounts, Operator shall refund Co-Owner the disputed amounts, including interest on the disputed amounts at the Late Payment Rate. 6.13 No Waiver of Right to Audit. Any payment made by a Co-Owner pursuant to this Agreement shall not constitute a waiver of any right of such Co-Owner to question or contest the accuracy of any charge, or to request and receive from Operator sufficient data to audit any charge concerning which a Co-Owner has a question or which is or may be contested, provided, however, that Co-Owner must initiate any audit or data request no later than twelve (12) months after the Due Date of any such bill or charge and bear reasonable costs associated with such audit, and provided further that if as a result of the audit a determination is made that errors were made by Operator, Operator shall, in addition to correcting the error, reimburse the costs of the audit to the Co-Owners. -9- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 6.14 Obligations. The Operator shall have no liability for any obligations except those expressly stated in this Agreement, and nothing in this Agreement shall obligate the Operator to perform any duties or assume any liabilities under any agreement to which the Operator is not directly a party unless such duties are also expressly stated in this Agreement, and then only to such extent. The Co-Owners acknowledge that the Operator’s performance under this Agreement is dependent upon the Co-Owners having complied with their obligations under this Agreement and the Operator having timely and appropriate access to all parts of the Shared Assets and access to all documents as reasonably required by the Operator. 6.15 Risk of Loss. As between the Co-Owners and the Operator, the Co-Owners shall be responsible for the risk of loss to the Shared Facilities or any portion thereof during the repair, management, operation and maintenance of the Shared Facilities, regardless of cause, except to the extent such loss is caused in whole or in part by the gross negligence or willful misconduct of the Operator. ARTICLE VII DAMAGE TO, DESTRUCTION OR FAILURE OF SHARED FACILITIES 7.1 Damage or Destruction. In the event of any damage or destruction to, or other failure of all or any part of the Shared Facilities that affects the business operations of one or more Co-Owners (each an “Affected Party”), such Affected Party shall, subject to any contrary requirements set forth in Material Project Agreements or by Applicable Law, take all commercially reasonable actions as may be necessary or appropriate to repair or replace the affected Shared Facilities or other facilities in order to restore the affected Shared Facilities or other facilities to substantially the same condition (or better) as before such damage or destruction (and any costs associated with such actions, after accounting for recoveries under any applicable insurance policies, will be shared by the Co-Owners pro rata based on their respective Proportionate Share, as applicable). Following any such damage, destruction or failure, if (i) the Affected Party fails to diligently proceed with the repair or replacement of the affected Shared Facilities or other facilities in accordance with the preceding sentence, or (ii) the Affected Party notifies the other Co-Owners that it does not intend to repair or replace the affected Shared Facilities or other facilities, then in either such case, the other Co-Owners shall have the right to repair or replace the affected Shared Facilities or other facilities (or a portion thereof sufficient to serve such other Co-Owners’ requirements) and continue the operation and maintenance thereof for the remainder of the Term; provided that in such event, the Affected Party shall be obligated to the Co-Owners funding the repair or replacement of the Shared Facilities to the extent of its Proportionate Share of the costs of repair or replacement; and provided further, that such other Co-Owners shall not unreasonably interfere with the business operations of the Affected Party. In all events, the Co-Owners shall cooperate with each other in good faith to minimize the impact thereof on the Co-Owners and their respective business operations. ARTICLE VIII CESSATION OF OPERATIONS BY A CO-OWNER 8.1 Co-Owner Ceasing Operations. In the event a Co-Owner anticipates shutting down, decommissioning, abandoning or ceasing the business operations of its Facility, (such Co- 10- 81078545.7 0081519-00002 Owner, a “Co-Owner Ceasing Business Operations”), it shall provide the other Co-Owners with at least six (6) months’ prior written notice of such planned shut-down, abandonment, decommissioning, or cessation of business operations, which notice shall indicate whether or not such Co-Owner Ceasing Business Operations relinquishes any option to rebuild its facilities or otherwise restart its operations within six (6) months after such cessation. The Co-Owner Ceasing Business Operations shall use commercially reasonable efforts under the circumstances to coordinate with the other Co-Owners in order to minimize any interference with such other Co- Owners’ business operations, and the Co-Owner Ceasing Business Operations shall, at the request of the other Co-Owners, take such actions, grant such rights, and execute and deliver such agreements, assignments, and instruments, including transfer and conveyance of its Ownership Interest in the Shared Assets in accordance with Section 8.3, subject to compliance with requirements of any Governmental Authority and Applicable Law. The remaining Co-Owners will assume decommissioning obligations for the Shared Facilities in accordance with their Proportionate Share of the Shared Assets acquired from the Co-Owner Ceasing Business Operations, and as may be reasonably necessary to enable such other Co-Owners to continue using, operating, and maintaining the Shared Facilities or to construct such additional facilities as may be necessary to replace such Shared Facilities, subject to the Co-Owner Ceasing Business Operation’s right to rebuild its facilities or otherwise restart its operations within six (6) months of the date of cessation of operations (if it has not relinquished the option to do so). After such planned abandonment, decommissioning, shut down or cessation of business operations by the Co- Owner Ceasing Business Operations, and until the Co-Owner Ceasing Business Operations determines to rebuild its facilities or otherwise restart its operations (within six months, if it has not relinquished its option to do so), the other Co-Owners shall assume and be responsible for all costs, liabilities and expenses associated with the use, operation, maintenance (and ownership and decommissioning, if applicable) of the Shared Facilities (and any other facilities that may become Shared Facilities). 8.2 Co-Owner Last Using Shared Facilities.
